news.title: Illegal colony options: Land for sewer line or demolition in Chandigarh
news.para: The act has prompted the UT administration to direct the municipal corporation (MC) to ask villagers to provide land for a pipeline to divert the sewage to a treatment plant or the illegal construction would be demolished to acquire the land.

news.title: Switch to unit area assessment or face 5% penalty: Kolkata civic body to taxpayers
news.para: The KMC assessment department will reserve the rights to levy a 5% penalty (maximum) annually on the property tax payers who won’t choose to switchover from the present rent-based annual valuation of the property.

news.title: Chandigarh administration issues 90 more notices for building misuse, violations
news.para: “A total of 65 notices have been served for misuse of properties and 25 for building violations,” said a UT official. It is also learnt that around 300 more notices are being in the process of being issued.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to help flat owners with speedy mutation
news.para: The objective is to also come to the rescue of flat-buyers, who are often burdened with the share of property tax that the developer of a housing project is supposed to clear.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board to auction 167 properties
news.para: The bidding process will start on November 25. The closing date for bid submission is December 20 and bids will be opened on December 20.

news.title: Funds allotted to fix deficient infrastructure in two more colonies in Gurugram
news.para: The department of town and country planning (DTCP), on May 9, had ordered takeover of nine private colonies after which, on June 15, MCG took over seven of these, including Ardee City as well as Sushant Lok-2 and 3.

news.title: Maharashtra to launch its own housing scheme for homeless people
news.para: A new target of 3.5 lakh homes has been set under Awaas plus which covers people who did not make it to the PMAY list.

news.title: Chandigarh administration to revise property collector rates
news.para: Collector rate is the minimum property value below which it cannot be registered with the government. On collector rate, stamp duty is also paid.

news.title: Aakash Educational Services' founder buys bungalow in Delhi for Rs 51 crore
news.para: "The Greater Kailash property has been bought from Infinity Buildwell and is spread across a 1,000 square yard plot."said one person familiar with the development.

news.title: Hyderabad: Karvy Group chairman booked for selling plots of 2009 sold-out venture
news.para: Earlier, police had registered cases based on complaints given by a few banks and Karvy’s investors, who were associated with its Karvy Stock Broking Limited (KSBL).

news.title: Greater Noida authority cancels allotment of two plots of Parsvnath Developers
news.para: ​Parsvnath Developers was allotted the two plots, measuring 25 acres and 8.5 acres in 2006 and 2007, respectively, for developing real estate projects by 2013 and 2012.

news.title: Allahabad HC disposes of RWA's plea against helipad in Jaypee Greens compound
news.para: Earlier this year, the RWA had moved the high court against Jaiprakash Associates Ltd (JAL), saying it had no permission from the Greater Noida Authority to operate the helipad amid villas and highrises.

news.title: High mortgage rates send homebuyers scrambling for relief
news.para: A recent snapshot by the Mortgage Bankers Association showed that ARMs accounted for 12.8% of all home loan applications in the week ended Oct. 14.

news.title: Government fixes Rs 7,409 crore indicative value for 'The Ashok' hotel
news.para: The Ashok and the adjacent hotel Samrat are among the eight India Tourism Development Corp assets listed under the National Monetisation Pipeline (NMP) announced by Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman last year.

news.title: China's bank sector issued $369 billion in real estate development loans in Jan-Oct 2022
news.para: Six of China's largest lenders have agreed to provide at least $130 in fresh credit to property developers, adding to recent regulatory support measures to ease a stifling cash crunch in the sector.
